        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 20 at 4:02PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Variadero, or 34 miles southwest of Mosquero,
moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Trementina.

This includes State Road 104 between Mile Markers 45 and 47.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
